title: Nike Releases Black Ohio State Shoes
text:
By 10TV Web Staff Thursday October 15, 2015 6:54 PM UPDATED: Thursday October 15, 2015 7:01 PM COLUMBUS, Ohio - 
On the heels of the black uniforms making their debut Saturday at Ohio Stadium , Nike has completed the outfit by releasing a new black shoe. 
Nike's website says "Train like your team with the Ohio State Nike Air Max Effort Trainer, completing the Black Pack for the October 17th game against Penn State." 
Nike had released another Ohio State shoe , as a part of their Week Zero collection, in August. 
The website says the shoes will cost $100 and go on sale Friday, October 16 at 10 a.m. 
You can get more information at Nike's website: http://swoo.sh/1Pw00C6 Â©2015 by 10TV.com.
